{"title_page": "Julian Perkins", "text_new": "{{short description|British early music conductor and keyboard player}}\n{{EngvarB|date=November 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2017}}\n\n[[File:Julian Perkins \u2013 conductor and keyboard player.jpg|thumb|Julian Perkins in rehearsal, 2012]]\n'''Julian Perkins''' is a British [[conducting|conductor]] and keyboard player ([[harpsichord]], [[fortepiano]] and [[clavichord]]).<ref>{{cite web|author=Andy Campbell |url=http://www.ncem.co.uk/?idno=160&action=s&stype=editrecord=true&by=p&media=0&keywords=&show=true&record=52 |title=The National Centre for Early Music \u2013 Early Music Directory |publisher=NCEM |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> He is Founder Director of the early music ensemble Sounds Baroque and Artistic Director of Cambridge Handel Opera Company.<ref>http://cambridgehandel.org.uk</ref>\n\nAs a conductor, Julian Perkins has been praised for his 'heartening dramatic energy' and 'dynamic direction',<ref>{{cite web|author=Lindsay Kemp |url=http://www.gramophone.co.uk/review/d-purcell-the-judgment-of-paris |title=D PURCELL The Judgment of Paris |website=Gramophone |date=2014-06-06 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Anna Picard |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/classical/reviews/edinburgh-festival-2013-classical-review-dido-and-aeneasbluebeards-castle-lament-for-broken-hearted-8792729.html |title=Edinburgh Festival 2013 classical review: Dido and Aeneas/Bluebeard's Castle: Lament for broken-hearted heroines |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |date=2013-08-31 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> while his harpsichord accompaniment has been described as 'superbly creative' and 'wonderfully adept and stylish'.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cooke |first=Rachel |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/music-and-performance/2013/09/breeches-brocade-and-bonbons |title=Breeches, brocade and bonbons |website=New Statesman |date=2013-09-26 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>http://www.criticscircle.org.uk/?ID=606&PID=5</ref> His solo discography includes premi\u00e8res of harpsichord suites by James Nares and John Christopher Smith,<ref>{{cite web|author=<!-- .article-image --> Title: Eight Harpsichord Setts |url=http://www.avie-records.com/releases/eight-harpsichord-setts |title=Eight Harpsichord Setts |publisher=Avie Records |date=2007-11-14 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chandos.net/products/catalogue/CHAN%200807 |title=Smith & Handel: Works for Harpsichord \u2013 Julian Perkins Harpsichord Early Music Chaconne |publisher=Chandos.net |date=2015-05-10 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> clavichord works by Herbert Howells and Stephen Dodgson,<ref>http://ascrecords.com/primafacie/howells_clavichord.html</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicweb-international.com/classrev/2009/Nov09/Dodgson_Dialogues_cameo2088.htm |title=DODGSON Diaalogues cameo2088 [WH&#93;: Classical CD Reviews \u2013 November 09 MusicWeb-International |publisher=Musicweb-international.com |date=2008-08-13 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> and Johann Sebastian Bach's ''French Suites'' on clavichord.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.resonusclassics.com/julian-perkins-bach-french-suites |title=J.S. Bach: French Suites, BWV 812\u2013817 &#124; RES10163 |publisher=Resonus Classics |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> He directed the first recording of Daniel Purcell's opera-oratorio ''The Judgment of Paris'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.resonusclassics.com/the-judgment-of-paris?filter_name=perkins |title=Daniel Purcell: The Judgment of Paris &#124; RES10128 |publisher=Resonusclassics.com |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> which he subsequently performed in London at [[St John's, Smith Square]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Valori |first=Charlotte |url=https://bachtrack.com/review-judgement-paris-purcell-march-2014 |title=The Also-Ran Who Outran Fate: Daniel Purcell's Judgement of Paris &#124; by Bachtrack for classical music, opera, ballet and dance event reviews |publisher=Bachtrack.com |date=2014-03-07 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> Other recordings include two discs of Italian cantatas and one of songs by Henry Purcell featuring the soprano Anna Dennis with Sounds Baroque.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avie-records.com/artists/julian-perkins/ |title=Julian Perkins |publisher=Avie Records |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>https://www.resonusclassics.com/sweeter-than-roses-henry-purcell-songs-anna-dennis-sounds-baroque-perins-res10235</ref> Duo recordings comprise Franz Schubert's violin sonatas of 1816 with Peter Sheppard Sk\u00e6rved and, with Emma Abbate, Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart's complete sonatas for keyboard duet and Carl Maria von Weber's complete works for keyboard duet.<ref>https://divineartrecords.com/recording/schubert-3-violin-sonatas/</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.resonusclassics.com/w-a-mozart-piano-duets-volume-1-emma-abbate-julian-perkins |title=W.A. Mozart: Piano Duets, Volume 1 &#124; Julian Perkins & Emma Abbate &#124; RES10172 |publisher=Resonus Classics |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>http://www.resonusclassics.com/mozart-piano-duets-volume-2-abbate-perkins-res10210</ref><ref>https://deux-elles.co.uk/product/carl-maria-von-weber-complete-keyboard-duets-dxl-1184/</ref> \n\nJulian Perkins has directed the [[Academy of Ancient Music]],<ref>https://www.cambridgeindependent.co.uk/whats-on/revew-john-eccles-semele-9091631/</ref> and performed concertos with [[Florilegium_(music_group)|Florilegium]], [[Orchestra of the Age of Enlightenment]], Orchestra of [[The Sixteen]] and [[Royal Northern Sinfonia]]. He works annually with the [[Southbank Sinfonia]], has conducted staged opera productions for organisations including the Buxton Festival,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artsderbyshire.org.uk/whats_on/details.asp?EventID=23926101 |title=Event details: Pimpinone |publisher=Artsderbyshire.org.uk |date=2011-07-17 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> Dutch National Opera Academy, Grimeborn Festival and Guildhall School of Music & Drama,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arcolatheatre.com/event/grimeborn-handel-furioso/?spektrix_bounce=true |title=Handel Furioso |publisher=Arcola Theatre |date=2013-08-27 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.operabase.com/listart.cgi?name=julian+perkins&acts=+Schedule+ |title=Julian Perkins, conductor :: Schedule |publisher=Operabase.com |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> and devised an opera pasticcio about [[Casanova]] with librettist Stephen Pettitt that he directed for the ''Baroque Unwrapped'' series at London's Kings Place in May 2016.<ref>{{cite web|author=oscar |url=http://www.camdenreview.com/node/992244 |title=Rich ingredients for seduction |publisher=Camden Review |date=2016-05-05 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> He has appeared live on BBC Radio 3,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07h6qll/clips |title=BBC Radio 3 \u2013 In Tune, Julian Perkins, Dominic Peckham, Tom Verney, Lucy Parham \u2013 Clips |publisher=BBC |date=1970-01-01 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> featured on ''The Early Music Show'' and contributed to the station's pioneering podcast about George Frideric Handel's ''Orlando'' with Welsh National Opera.<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09r3qj1</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/events/en4v2m/live/czdg9r# |title=Opera on 3 \u2013 Handel's Orlando |publisher=BBC |date=2015-11-07 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> Since 2014, Julian Perkins has been the Artistic Director of Coram's ''Handel Birthday Concert'',<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8BWliZhRWvE&list=PLv2p59eiUTbeYNb1N4DndYF1AP4_IYtZ8</ref> that raises money for vulnerable children. He has given solo recitals in international festivals at St Albans, Buxton, Canterbury, Deal, King's Lynn, Lammermuir, Northern Aldborough, Oundle, Petworth, Roman River, Ryedale, Swaledale, Two Moors and Tel Aviv. He wrote an introduction to the clavichord for ''BBC Music Magazine'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.classical-music.com/article/what-clavichord |title=What is a... Clavichord? |website=BBC Music Magazine |date=2016-06-16 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> and his article about John Christopher Smith was published by ''Early Music Today''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pocketmags.com/early-music-today-magazine/june-aug-2015 |title=Early Music Today Magazine \u2013 June \u2013 Aug 2015 Subscriptions |publisher=Pocketmags.com |date=2012-11-23 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> He is a harpsichord tutor at the [[Royal Northern College of Music]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rncm.ac.uk/people/julian-perkins/ |title=Julian Perkins \u2013 Royal Northern College of Music |website=Rncm.ac.uk |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://julianperkins.com/ Official website]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCXULdyC7dmOaMlkB8zv77gw?feature=em-share_video_user Official YouTube channel]\n*[http://cambridgehandel.org.uk Official website for Cambridge Handel Opera Company]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Perkins, Julian}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:British conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:British male conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:English harpsichordists]]\n[[Category:Fortepianists]]\n[[Category:Clavichordists]]\n[[Category:British performers of early music]]\n[[Category:Bach musicians]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal College of Organists]]\n[[Category:Alumni of King's College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Royal Academy of Music]]\n[[Category:Schola Cantorum Basiliensis alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:Choral Scholars of the Choir of King's College, Cambridge]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British early music conductor and keyboard player}}\n{{EngvarB|date=November 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2017}}\n\n[[File:Julian Perkins \u2013 conductor and keyboard player.jpg|thumb|Julian Perkins \u2013 conductor and keyboard player]]\n'''Julian Perkins''' is a British [[conducting|conductor]] and keyboard player ([[harpsichord]], [[fortepiano]] and [[clavichord]]).<ref>{{cite web|author=Andy Campbell |url=http://www.ncem.co.uk/?idno=160&action=s&stype=editrecord=true&by=p&media=0&keywords=&show=true&record=52 |title=The National Centre for Early Music \u2013 Early Music Directory |publisher=NCEM |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> He is Founder Director of the early music ensemble Sounds Baroque and Artistic Director of Cambridge Handel Opera Company.<ref>http://cambridgehandel.org.uk</ref>\n\nAs a conductor, Julian Perkins has been praised for his 'heartening dramatic energy' and 'dynamic direction',<ref>{{cite web|author=Lindsay Kemp |url=http://www.gramophone.co.uk/review/d-purcell-the-judgment-of-paris |title=D PURCELL The Judgment of Paris |website=Gramophone |date=2014-06-06 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Anna Picard |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/classical/reviews/edinburgh-festival-2013-classical-review-dido-and-aeneasbluebeards-castle-lament-for-broken-hearted-8792729.html |title=Edinburgh Festival 2013 classical review: Dido and Aeneas/Bluebeard's Castle: Lament for broken-hearted heroines |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |date=2013-08-31 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> while his harpsichord accompaniment has been described as 'superbly creative' and 'wonderfully adept and stylish'.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cooke |first=Rachel |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/music-and-performance/2013/09/breeches-brocade-and-bonbons |title=Breeches, brocade and bonbons |website=New Statesman |date=2013-09-26 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>http://www.criticscircle.org.uk/?ID=606&PID=5</ref> His solo discography includes premi\u00e8res of harpsichord suites by James Nares and John Christopher Smith,<ref>{{cite web|author=<!-- .article-image --> Title: Eight Harpsichord Setts |url=http://www.avie-records.com/releases/eight-harpsichord-setts |title=Eight Harpsichord Setts |publisher=Avie Records |date=2007-11-14 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chandos.net/products/catalogue/CHAN%200807 |title=Smith & Handel: Works for Harpsichord \u2013 Julian Perkins Harpsichord Early Music Chaconne |publisher=Chandos.net |date=2015-05-10 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> clavichord works by Herbert Howells and Stephen Dodgson,<ref>http://ascrecords.com/primafacie/howells_clavichord.html</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicweb-international.com/classrev/2009/Nov09/Dodgson_Dialogues_cameo2088.htm |title=DODGSON Diaalogues cameo2088 [WH&#93;: Classical CD Reviews \u2013 November 09 MusicWeb-International |publisher=Musicweb-international.com |date=2008-08-13 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> and Johann Sebastian Bach's ''French Suites'' on clavichord.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.resonusclassics.com/julian-perkins-bach-french-suites |title=J.S. Bach: French Suites, BWV 812\u2013817 &#124; RES10163 |publisher=Resonus Classics |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> He directed the first recording of Daniel Purcell's opera-oratorio ''The Judgment of Paris'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.resonusclassics.com/the-judgment-of-paris?filter_name=perkins |title=Daniel Purcell: The Judgment of Paris &#124; RES10128 |publisher=Resonusclassics.com |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> which he subsequently performed in London at [[St John's, Smith Square]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Valori |first=Charlotte |url=https://bachtrack.com/review-judgement-paris-purcell-march-2014 |title=The Also-Ran Who Outran Fate: Daniel Purcell's Judgement of Paris &#124; by Bachtrack for classical music, opera, ballet and dance event reviews |publisher=Bachtrack.com |date=2014-03-07 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> Other recordings include two discs of Italian cantatas and one of songs by Henry Purcell featuring the soprano Anna Dennis with Sounds Baroque.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avie-records.com/artists/julian-perkins/ |title=Julian Perkins |publisher=Avie Records |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>https://www.resonusclassics.com/sweeter-than-roses-henry-purcell-songs-anna-dennis-sounds-baroque-perins-res10235</ref> Duo recordings comprise Franz Schubert's violin sonatas of 1816 with Peter Sheppard Sk\u00e6rved and, with Emma Abbate, Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart's complete sonatas for keyboard duet and Carl Maria von Weber's complete works for keyboard duet.<ref>https://divineartrecords.com/recording/schubert-3-violin-sonatas/</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.resonusclassics.com/w-a-mozart-piano-duets-volume-1-emma-abbate-julian-perkins |title=W.A. Mozart: Piano Duets, Volume 1 &#124; Julian Perkins & Emma Abbate &#124; RES10172 |publisher=Resonus Classics |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>http://www.resonusclassics.com/mozart-piano-duets-volume-2-abbate-perkins-res10210</ref><ref>https://deux-elles.co.uk/product/carl-maria-von-weber-complete-keyboard-duets-dxl-1184/</ref> \n\nJulian Perkins has directed the [[Academy of Ancient Music]],<ref>https://www.cambridgeindependent.co.uk/whats-on/revew-john-eccles-semele-9091631/</ref> and performed concertos with [[Florilegium_(music_group)|Florilegium]], [[Orchestra of the Age of Enlightenment]], Orchestra of [[The Sixteen]] and [[Royal Northern Sinfonia]]. He works annually with the [[Southbank Sinfonia]], has conducted staged opera productions for organisations including the Buxton Festival,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artsderbyshire.org.uk/whats_on/details.asp?EventID=23926101 |title=Event details: Pimpinone |publisher=Artsderbyshire.org.uk |date=2011-07-17 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> Dutch National Opera Academy, Grimeborn Festival and Guildhall School of Music & Drama,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arcolatheatre.com/event/grimeborn-handel-furioso/?spektrix_bounce=true |title=Handel Furioso |publisher=Arcola Theatre |date=2013-08-27 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.operabase.com/listart.cgi?name=julian+perkins&acts=+Schedule+ |title=Julian Perkins, conductor :: Schedule |publisher=Operabase.com |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> and devised an opera pasticcio about [[Casanova]] with librettist Stephen Pettitt that he directed for the ''Baroque Unwrapped'' series at London's Kings Place in May 2016.<ref>{{cite web|author=oscar |url=http://www.camdenreview.com/node/992244 |title=Rich ingredients for seduction |publisher=Camden Review |date=2016-05-05 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> He has appeared live on BBC Radio 3,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07h6qll/clips |title=BBC Radio 3 \u2013 In Tune, Julian Perkins, Dominic Peckham, Tom Verney, Lucy Parham \u2013 Clips |publisher=BBC |date=1970-01-01 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> featured on ''The Early Music Show'' and contributed to the station's pioneering podcast about George Frideric Handel's ''Orlando'' with Welsh National Opera.<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09r3qj1</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/events/en4v2m/live/czdg9r# |title=Opera on 3 \u2013 Handel's Orlando |publisher=BBC |date=2015-11-07 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> Since 2014, Julian Perkins has been the Artistic Director of Coram's ''Handel Birthday Concert'',<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8BWliZhRWvE&list=PLv2p59eiUTbeYNb1N4DndYF1AP4_IYtZ8</ref> that raises money for vulnerable children. He has given solo recitals in international festivals at St Albans, Buxton, Canterbury, Deal, King's Lynn, Lammermuir, Northern Aldborough, Oundle, Petworth, Roman River, Ryedale, Swaledale, Two Moors and Tel Aviv. He wrote an introduction to the clavichord for ''BBC Music Magazine'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.classical-music.com/article/what-clavichord |title=What is a... Clavichord? |website=BBC Music Magazine |date=2016-06-16 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> and his article about John Christopher Smith was published by ''Early Music Today''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pocketmags.com/early-music-today-magazine/june-aug-2015 |title=Early Music Today Magazine \u2013 June \u2013 Aug 2015 Subscriptions |publisher=Pocketmags.com |date=2012-11-23 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> He is a harpsichord tutor at the [[Royal Northern College of Music]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rncm.ac.uk/people/julian-perkins/ |title=Julian Perkins \u2013 Royal Northern College of Music |website=Rncm.ac.uk |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://julianperkins.com/ Official website]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCXULdyC7dmOaMlkB8zv77gw?feature=em-share_video_user Official YouTube channel]\n*[http://cambridgehandel.org.uk Official website for Cambridge Handel Opera Company]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Perkins, Julian}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:British conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:British male conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:English harpsichordists]]\n[[Category:Fortepianists]]\n[[Category:Clavichordists]]\n[[Category:British performers of early music]]\n[[Category:Bach musicians]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal College of Organists]]\n[[Category:Alumni of King's College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Royal Academy of Music]]\n[[Category:Schola Cantorum Basiliensis alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:Choral Scholars of the Choir of King's College, Cambridge]]\n", "name_user": "Trillsintime", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julian_Perkins"}
